# C# Variable Naming

Do not start variable names with `_`.

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
private int _level;
var _monsterType = MonsterType.Палочник;

// ✅ GOOD
private int level;
var monsterType = MonsterType.Палочник;
```

This applies to locals, parameters, fields, and other variables. Use ordinary camelCase for locals/parameters and PascalCase for public members per normal C# conventions.

When editing existing code, follow the naming style already used in that file unless you are explicitly renaming as part of the task.
